questions.question:
What will TypeScript report for this code?

```ts
const arr: readonly number[] = [1, 2, 3];
arr.push(4);
```

What does the spread operator do with arrays?

```ts
const a = [1, 2];
const b = [3, 4];
const c = [...a, ...b];
```

What happens when you access an index beyond a tuple's defined length?

```ts
const pair: [string, number] = ['hello', 42];
const val = pair[5];
```

What does this code produce?

```ts
const obj = { x: 1, y: 2 };
const { x, y } = obj;
console.log(x, y);
```

What does the spread operator do with objects?

```ts
const a = { x: 1, y: 2 };
const b = { y: 3, z: 4 };
const c = { ...a, ...b };
```

What error does this code produce?

```ts
const person: { readonly name: string } = { name: 'Alice' };
person.name = 'Bob';
```

What does TypeScript infer for the destructured variable `b` here?

```ts
const data: [number, string, boolean] = [1, 'two', true];
const [a, b, c] = data;
```
